title: Nature's balance is an illusion.
pid: e1d6664c-9b8d-434a-808d-18d06757d217
body: |2-
  c.f. Stephen Harding and James Lovelock's "Daisyworld" experiments.

  Nature can have a long-running stable equilibria, but over the long term
  -- and sometimes even the shockingly short term --
  they are ephemeral.
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
